This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) because it presents a novel approach to ontology reasoning that is based on deep learning. It is also likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) because it introduces a new model for statistical relational learning that is built upon deep recursive neural networks. Additionally, it could belong to the sub-category of Databases (cs.DB) because it deals with ontology reasoning, which is a fundamental problem in database management. It could also belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL) because it involves natural language processing and semantic understanding. Finally, it could belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) because it uses deep neural networks for ontology reasoning.
